roti), naan (made from refined wheat flour, and cooked in a clay tandoori oven), puri (deep-fried and puffed up bread), and many more. a typical meal consists of one or more gravy dishes along with rotis, to be eaten by breaking off a piece of roti, dipping it in the gravy and eating them together. most of the hindi heartland of india survives on roti, rice, and lentils (dal), which are prepared in several different ways and made spicy to taste. served on the side, you will usually find spiced yogurt (raita) and either fresh chutney or a tiny piece 